{"title_page": "1992\u201393 Czechoslovak First League", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n | competition        = [[Czechoslovak First League]]\n | season             = 1992\u201393\n | winners            = [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]]\n | relegated          = none\n | continentalcup1    = [[1993\u201394 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]]\n | continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]]\n | continentalcup2    = [[1993\u201394 European Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]]\n | continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[FC Zbrojovka Brno|Boby Brno]]\n | continentalcup3    = [[1993\u201394 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]]\n | continentalcup3 qualifiers = [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]]<br/>[[\u0160K Slovan Bratislava|Slovan Bratislava]]<br/>[[DAC 1904 Dunajsk\u00e1 Streda|Dunajsk\u00e1 Streda]]\n | league topscorer   = [[Peter Dubovsk\u00fd (footballer)|Peter Dubovsk\u00fd]] (24 goals)\n | biggest home win   = \n | biggest away win   = \n | highest scoring    = \n | matches            = \n | total goals        = \n<!--\nNOTE: The following parameters require attached reliable sources when used!\n-->\n | longest wins       = \n | longest unbeaten   = \n | longest losses     = \n | highest attendance = \n | lowest attendance  = \n | average attendance = \n | prevseason         = [[1991\u201392 Czechoslovak First League|1991\u201392]]\n | nextseason         = [[1993\u201394 Czech First League|1993\u201394 Czech Republic]]<br>[[1993\u201394 Slovak Superliga|1993\u201394 Slovakia]]\n}}\nThe 1992\u201393 season of the [[Czechoslovak First League]] was the last in which teams from the [[Czech Republic]] and [[Slovakia]] competed together. [[Peter Dubovsk\u00fd (footballer)|Peter Dubovsk\u00fd]] was the league's top scorer with 24 goals.<ref>{{cite book|first=Lubo\u0161|last=Je\u0159\u00e1bek|title=\u010cesk\u00fd a \u010deskoslovensk\u00fd fotbal - lexikon osobnost\u00ed a klub\u016f|publisher=Grada Publishing|language=Czech|year=2007|location=Prague, Czech Republic|isbn=978-80-247-1656-5|page=232}}</ref> The league was succeeded at the end of the season by the [[Czech First League]] and the [[Slovak Super Liga]].\n\n==Overview==\nIt was contested by 16 teams, and [[Sparta Prague]] won the championship. Czechoslovakia received one of the slots of [[UN]] banned [[Yugoslavia]] for the UEFA Cup. Brno was invited as Czech club to the Cup Winners Cup because the Cup of Czechoslovakia went to Slovakia and the loser finalist was Sparta Prague.\n\n==League standings==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=SPA|name_SPA=[[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]]\n|team2=SLA|name_SLA=[[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]]\n|team3=SLO|name_SLO=[[\u0160K Slovan Bratislava|Slovan Bratislava]]\n|team4=DAC|name_DAC=[[FC DAC 1904 Dunajsk\u00e1 Streda|DAC Dunajsk\u00e1 Streda]]\n|team5=SIG|name_SIG=[[SK Sigma Olomouc|Sigma Olomouc]]\n|team6=OST|name_OST=[[FC Ban\u00edk Ostrava|Ban\u00edk Ostrava]]\n|team7=BRA|name_BRA=[[FK Inter Bratislava|Inter Bratislava]]\n|team8=BRN|name_BRN=[[FC Zbrojovka Brno|Boby Brno]]\n|team9=HRK|name_HRK=[[FC Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9|Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9]]\n|team10=VIT|name_VIT=[[MFK V\u00edtkovice|V\u00edtkovice]]\n|team11=TAT|name_TAT=[[1. FC Tatran Pre\u0161ov|Tatran Pre\u0161ov]]\n|team12=NIT|name_NIT=[[FC Nitra|Nitra]]\n|team13=\u010cBU|name_\u010cBU=[[SK Dynamo \u010cesk\u00e9 Bud\u011bjovice|\u010cesk\u00e9 Bud\u011bjovice]]\n|team14=DUK|name_DUK=[[Dukla Prague]]\n|team15=B05|name_B05=[[Bohemians 1905|Bohemians Prague]]\n|team16=TRV|name_TRV=[[FC Spartak Trnava|Spartak Trnava]]\n|win_SPA=23|draw_SPA=2|loss_SPA=5|gf_SPA=66|ga_SPA=24|status_SPA=C\n|win_SLA=18|draw_SLA=7|loss_SLA=5|gf_SLA=70|ga_SLA=28\n|win_SLO=19|draw_SLO=4|loss_SLO=7|gf_SLO=61|ga_SLO=31\n|win_DAC=16|draw_DAC=5|loss_DAC=9|gf_DAC=46|ga_DAC=36\n|win_SIG=14|draw_SIG=7|loss_SIG=9|gf_SIG=44|ga_SIG=38\n|win_OST=10|draw_OST=11|loss_OST=9|gf_OST=47|ga_OST=38\n|win_BRA=14|draw_BRA=3|loss_BRA=13|gf_BRA=46|ga_BRA=42\n|win_BRN=13|draw_BRN=5|loss_BRN=12|gf_BRN=40|ga_BRN=51\n|win_HRK=10|draw_HRK=7|loss_HRK=13|gf_HRK=32|ga_HRK=36\n|win_VIT=9|draw_VIT=9|loss_VIT=12|gf_VIT=30|ga_VIT=44\n|win_TAT=9|draw_TAT=8|loss_TAT=13|gf_TAT=42|ga_TAT=40\n|win_NIT=6|draw_NIT=13|loss_NIT=11|gf_NIT=27|ga_NIT=38\n|win_\u010cBU=9|draw_\u010cBU=5|loss_\u010cBU=16|gf_\u010cBU=36|ga_\u010cBU=39\n|win_DUK=7|draw_DUK=5|loss_DUK=18|gf_DUK=38|ga_DUK=74\n|win_B05=5|draw_B05=9|loss_B05=16|gf_B05=23|ga_B05=53\n|win_TRV=3|draw_TRV=10|loss_TRV=17|gf_TRV=24|ga_TRV=60\n\n|col_UCL=green1|text_UCL=Qualification for [[1993\u201394 UEFA Champions League#First round|Champions League first round]]\n|result1=UCL\n|col_UC=blue1|text_UC=Qualification for [[1993\u201394 UEFA Cup#First round|UEFA Cup first round]]\n|result2=UC\n|col_UCSL=blue1|text_UCSL={{fb multicomp\n |bc1=blue1|competition1=Qualification for [[1993\u201394 UEFA Cup#First round|UEFA Cup first round]]\n |bc2=yellow1|competition2=Moving to [[1993\u201394 Slovak Superliga|Slovak Superliga]]\n }}\n|result3=UCSL|result4=UCSL\n|col_SL=yellow1|text_SL=Moving to [[1993\u201394 Slovak Superliga|Slovak Superliga]]\n|result7=SL|result11=SL|result12=SL|result16=SL\n|col_CWC=lightgreen|text_CWC=Qualification for [[1993\u201394 European Cup Winners' Cup#First round|Cup Winners' Cup first round]]\n|note_res_CWC=Boby Brno were invited to represent Czech Republic in the [[1993\u201394 European Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]] as Czech Cup runners-up (semifinal phase of Czechoslovak Cup).<br>[[FC VSS Ko\u0161ice|Ko\u0161ice]] were the winners of Czechoslovak Cup but were represented Slovakia in the Cup Winners' Cup.\n|result8=CWC\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*[http://www.rsssf.com/tablest/tsjslhist.html Czechoslovakia - List of final tables (RSSSF)]\n\n{{Czechoslovak First League seasons}}\n{{1992\u201393 in European Football (UEFA)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1992-93 Czechoslovak First League}}\n[[Category:Czechoslovak First League seasons]]\